<TITLE> MDC says to debate Zimbabwe run-off withdrawal soon </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 HARARE, Sun Jun 22, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Zimbabwe's opposition will begin a meeting shortly to discuss its possible withdrawal from the June 27 presidential run-off election, which has been marred by escalating violence, a party spokesman said on Sunday. "We have to evaluate whether it is worth spilling blood in the name of an election. The MDC national council will begin meeting shortly to decide on that," MDC spokesman Nelson Chamisa told Reuters
